      <!-- Dorobant -->
      <string _locid="77182020">Dorobant</string>
      <string _locid="77182021">Romanian musket infantry. The Dorobanți were professional foot soldiers who served the Wallachian and Moldavian princes. Slightly tougher than standard Musketeers, reflecting Romania's tradition of resilient frontier warriors.</string>
      <string _locid="77182022">Dorobant</string>

      <!-- Romanian Pandur -->
      <string _locid="77182030">Romanian Pandur</string>
      <string _locid="77182031">Romanian light skirmisher infantry. Similar to Hungarian Pandurs but adapted to Romanian forest warfare. Effective against cavalry units.</string>
      <string _locid="77182032">Romanian Pandur</string>

      <!-- Seimeni -->
      <string _locid="77182040">Seimeni</string>
      <string _locid="77182041">Romanian pike infantry. The Seimeni were elite infantry guards of the Romanian princes, armed with pikes and trained to resist cavalry charges. The toughest infantry in the Romanian roster.</string>
      <string _locid="77182042">Seimeni</string>

      <!-- Curteni -->
      <string _locid="77182050">Curteni</string>
      <string _locid="77182051">Romanian noble cavalry. The Curteni were the household cavalry of Romanian princes, equivalent to hussar-type units but with a distinctly Eastern European fighting style.</string>
